If you want cheap Latin eats this place is for you. It is a hole in the wall spot with a few tables. Suggest you take a look and order whatever you see that is fresh, or cooked to order. The portions are quite large. Two pork chops were quick fried, served with rice, beans, and a salad. Ribs were grilled, served with fried plantain, tostones. We had 2 cokes and were set back just $25, not bad at all considering each meal was actually big enough for 2 people! So try it out if your on a budget, hungry, and especially if you love roast pork shoulder, pernil.
